The paper proposes an extension of CDCL-based SAT solvers to deal with the problem of enumerating all models of a Boolean formula in CNF. This problem is related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as it involves solving logical problems. The paper also provides an experimental evaluation of the proposed algorithms on satisfiable SAT instances, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper deals with sequence mining problems, which are related to data structures (cs.DS) and data mining (cs.DM). Finally, the paper proposes an extension of SAT solvers, which falls under the category of programming languages (cs.PL).
